HEADWORD: Sulphone
<hw>Sul"phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a series of compounds analogous to the ketones, and
consisting of the sulphuryl group united with two hydrocarbon radicals;
<as>as, dimethyl <ex>sulphone</ex>, (CH<?/)<?/</as>.SO<?/.</def>⟦br⟧
